<ul class="list-none space-y-4 p-0 m-0" style="color: var(--outline-dark);">
    <li class="space-y-2">
        <p>Guess the hidden word in 6 tries.</p>
        <p>Each guess must be a valid 5 letter word. Hit the enter button to submit the guess.</p>
        <p>After your submission, the color of the tiles will change as in the examples below.</p>
    </li>
    <li class="border-t my-2" style="border-color: var(--outline-dark);"></li>
    <li class="flex justify-start flex-wrap gap-1">
        <div class="wordle-example-tile" style="background-color: var(--correct); color: var(--correct-text);"><span>G</span></div>
        <div class="wordle-example-tile" style="background-color: var(--bg-cream); color: var(--key-default-text);"><span>A</span></div>
        <div class="wordle-example-tile" style="background-color: var(--bg-cream); color: var(--key-default-text);"><span>M</span></div>
        <div class="wordle-example-tile" style="background-color: var(--bg-cream); color: var(--key-default-text);"><span>E</span></div>
        <div class="wordle-example-tile" style="background-color: var(--bg-cream); color: var(--key-default-text);"><span>S</span></div>
    </li>
    <li><p>The letter <strong>G</strong> is in the word and in the correct spot.</p></li>
    <li class="flex justify-start flex-wrap gap-1">
        <div class="wordle-example-tile" style="background-color: var(--bg-cream); color: var(--key-default-text);"><span>H</span></div>
        <div class="wordle-example-tile" style="background-color: var(--wrong-spot); color: var(--wrong-spot-text);"><span>O</span></div>
        <div class="wordle-example-tile" style="background-color: var(--bg-cream); color: var(--key-default-text);"><span>T</span></div>
        <div class="wordle-example-tile" style="background-color: var(--bg-cream); color: var(--key-default-text);"><span>E</span></div>
        <div class="wordle-example-tile" style="background-color: var(--bg-cream); color: var(--key-default-text);"><span>L</span></div>
    </li>
    <li><p>The letter <strong>O</strong> is in the word but in the wrong spot.</p></li>
    <li class="flex justify-start flex-wrap gap-1">
        <div class="wordle-example-tile" style="background-color: var(--absent); color: var(--absent-text);"><span>C</span></div>
        <div class="wordle-example-tile" style="background-color: var(--bg-cream); color: var(--key-default-text);"><span>L</span></div>
        <div class="wordle-example-tile" style="background-color: var(--bg-cream); color: var(--key-default-text);"><span>I</span></div>
        <div class="wordle-example-tile" style="background-color: var(--absent); color: var(--absent-text);"><span>C</span></div>
        <div class="wordle-example-tile" style="background-color: var(--bg-cream); color: var(--key-default-text);"><span>K</span></div>
    </li>
    <li><p>The letter <strong>C</strong> is not in the word in any spot.</p></li>
</ul>
<button type="button" class="w-full mt-4 wordle-btn-primary py-2 px-4 rounded font-semibold" @onclick="Submit">Close</button>

@code {
    [Parameter] public EventCallback OnClose { get; set; }

    private async Task Submit() => await OnClose.InvokeAsync();
}
